# SOC Home Lab - Splunk, Sysmon and Adversary Simulation

## Overview

This project demonstrates the creation of an isolated Security Operations Center (SOC) home lab using VirtualBox to simulate attacker and defender activities within a controlled environment.

The objective of the project was to gain hands-on experience with endpoint telemetry collection, attack simulation, log analysis and incident investigation using technologies commonly found in enterprise environments.

The lab consists of a Windows 10 endpoint configured with Sysmon and Splunk Enterprise, alongside a Kali Linux attacker machine used for adversary emulation activities.

## Technologies Used

* VirtualBox
* Windows 10
* Kali Linux
* Splunk Enterprise
* Sysmon
* Metasploit Framework
* MSFVenom
* MITRE ATT&CK Framework

