## Objectives

* Build an isolated enterprise-style SOC environment.
* Collect detailed endpoint telemetry using Sysmon.
* Ingest and analyse logs within Splunk.
* Simulate attacker behaviour using Metasploit and MSFVenom.
* Investigate attack artefacts generated during compromise simulation.
* Map observed activity to MITRE ATT&CK techniques.

## Attack Scenario

A Meterpreter reverse shell payload was generated using MSFVenom and executed on the Windows 10 endpoint from the Kali Linux attack host.

The attack generated telemetry across process creation, command execution and network connection events, which were subsequently analysed using Splunk and Sysmon logs.

## Key Investigation Areas

* Process creation analysis using Sysmon Event ID 1.
* Network connection analysis using Sysmon Event ID 3.
* Parent-child process relationship reconstruction.
* Reverse shell communication analysis.
* MITRE ATT&CK technique mapping.

